OL,6,F"This was an appalling piece of
OL,7,Fdriving. You had held a driving
OL,8,Flicence for no more than a year.
OL,10,F"You were therefore on any view an
OL,11,Finexperienced driver.
OL,13,F"You had not actually taken the
OL,14,Ftrouble to familiarise yourself with
OL,15,Fsolid white lines and what they mean,
OL,16,Fwhat they are there for."
OL,18,FHe continued: "Although you say you
OL,19,Fwere doing 'follow the leader' the
OL,20,Fresponsibility for this accident rests
OL,21,Fsolely with you."
